That intelligence field,
the big field in the sky.

00:17:52.038 --> 00:17:53.506 align:middle line:84%
However you want
to talk about it.

00:17:53.506 --> 00:17:55.741 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The human energy
field, the quantum field.

00:17:55.741 --> 00:17:57.276 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Give it any
name you want to.

00:17:57.276 --> 00:17:58.277 align:middle line:90%
It's more than human.

00:17:58.277 --> 00:18:01.080 align:middle line:84%
It could be any-- could be
all animal life gets it.

00:18:01.080 --> 00:18:02.682 align:middle line:90%
And all rocks get it.

00:18:02.682 --> 00:18:03.916 align:middle line:90%
And everybody gets it.

00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:05.885 align:middle line:90%
So it's a big field--

00:18:05.885 --> 00:18:07.553 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That Fred
calls the mind of God.

00:18:07.553 --> 00:18:08.988 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: I call it
the mind of God.

00:18:08.988 --> 00:18:14.560 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is
it projects via light

00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:18.831 align:middle line:84%
into whatever
space, time, matter,

00:18:18.831 --> 00:18:23.569 align:middle line:84%
particulate of where you are
at any particular moment.

00:18:23.569 --> 00:18:26.505 align:middle line:84%
And at that moment,
it also provides you

00:18:26.505 --> 00:18:34.280 align:middle line:84%
with an identification procedure
in which you say I am here now.

00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:35.014 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:18:35.014 --> 00:18:36.983 align:middle line:84%
So that's how--
that is basically

00:18:36.983 --> 00:18:40.853 align:middle line:84%
how the entire field--
this holographic illusion--

00:18:40.853 --> 00:18:44.123 align:middle line:84%
from the observer, from us the
observer, says we are here now.

00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:50.429 align:middle line:84%
So can we, indeed, observe
our past differently?

00:18:50.429 --> 00:18:51.864 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: We can
observe anything we

00:18:51.864 --> 00:18:55.401 align:middle line:84%
want if we begin the
identification process that I

00:18:55.401 --> 00:18:58.771 align:middle line:84%
mentioned to you, which is to
stop identifying with the here

00:18:58.771 --> 00:18:59.805 align:middle line:90%
and now.

00:18:59.805 --> 00:19:01.774 align:middle line:84%
Because the here
and now-- I mean,

00:19:01.774 --> 00:19:04.643 align:middle line:84%
all the greats spiritual
teachers said be here now.

00:19:04.643 --> 00:19:06.412 align:middle line:84%
Well, it turns
out that's as much

00:19:06.412 --> 00:19:08.948 align:middle line:84%
of a fantasy as
what you might think

00:19:08.948 --> 00:19:10.216 align:middle line:90%
anything I'm saying right here.

00:19:10.216 --> 00:19:11.484 align:middle line:90%
You can't be here, now.

00:19:11.484 --> 00:19:15.321 align:middle line:84%
Because there is
no here now to be.

00:19:15.321 --> 00:19:16.489 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a good point.

00:19:16.489 --> 00:19:20.559 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: So, the whole point is
you're everywhere, at all time.

00:19:20.559 --> 00:19:23.763 align:middle line:84%
And that's the real reality
of who and what you are.

00:19:23.763 --> 00:19:26.165 align:middle line:84%
And so, being here,
now, focusing in,

00:19:26.165 --> 00:19:30.436 align:middle line:84%
which is part of what
I teach in my books

00:19:30.436 --> 00:19:32.972 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, that's
part of the process.

00:19:32.972 --> 00:19:36.409 align:middle line:84%
If you understand that it's
a process that you can learn,

00:19:36.409 --> 00:19:39.111 align:middle line:84%
then you can begin to
identify with that which

00:19:39.111 --> 00:19:42.548 align:middle line:84%
is making that process, rather
than identify with the process

00:19:42.548 --> 00:19:43.616 align:middle line:90%
and be stuck in it.

00:19:43.616 --> 00:19:44.116 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:19:44.116 --> 00:19:46.085 align:middle line:84%
So I want to go back to
our Facebook questions.

00:19:46.085 --> 00:19:47.586 align:middle line:84%
And it basically
says, will this--

00:19:47.586 --> 00:19:51.190 align:middle line:84%
how will this lead us
into a sustainable future?

00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:54.293 align:middle line:84%
How will this whole
concept of quantum physics

00:19:54.293 --> 00:19:55.995 align:middle line:90%
lead us to a sustainable future?

00:19:55.995 --> 00:19:58.431 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Well, what does it mean
to be a sustainable future?

00:19:58.431 --> 00:20:01.834 align:middle line:84%
What does it mean
to be sustainable?

00:20:01.834 --> 00:20:03.169 align:middle line:90%
Having enough to eat?

00:20:03.169 --> 00:20:04.770 align:middle line:90%
Having enough money to spend?

00:20:04.770 --> 00:20:06.305 align:middle line:90%
Having enough clothes to wear?

00:20:06.305 --> 00:20:07.773 align:middle line:90%
Having enough air to breathe?

00:20:07.773 --> 00:20:08.374 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Enough.

00:20:08.374 --> 00:20:08.874 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: OK.

00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:13.112 align:middle line:84%
If we can imagine those
things-- if we can imagine them,

00:20:13.112 --> 00:20:16.515 align:middle line:84%
then we can imagine-- we can
allow our dreams to tell us

00:20:16.515 --> 00:20:21.053 align:middle line:84%
what we need to do to
improve the situation,

00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:26.225 align:middle line:84%
or make it better, or make
it more real for other people

00:20:26.225 --> 00:20:27.793 align:middle line:90%
who are suffering.

00:20:27.793 --> 00:20:29.228 align:middle line:84%
There's still lots
of people that

00:20:29.228 --> 00:20:32.231 align:middle line:84%
don't have enough of
the things that we

00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:34.033 align:middle line:84%
may want to have
more of, they don't

00:20:34.033 --> 00:20:35.835 align:middle line:90%
have enough of to begin with.

00:20:35.835 --> 00:20:38.304 align:middle line:84%
So we have to begin
to think globally

00:20:38.304 --> 00:20:39.772 align:middle line:90%
about the whole situation.

00:20:39.772 --> 00:20:41.574 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So we really
can affect this

00:20:41.574 --> 00:20:42.975 align:middle line:84%
with our collective
consciousness.

00:20:42.975 --> 00:20:44.477 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: We're doing
it all the time.

00:20:44.477 --> 00:20:45.644 align:middle line:90%
We're doing it all the time.

00:20:45.644 --> 00:20:49.915 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the mind is more than
just the individual mind.

00:20:49.915 --> 00:20:55.754 align:middle line:84%
And when events start to happen,
they happen everywhere at once.

00:20:55.754 --> 00:20:58.390 align:middle line:84%
They don't just happen in
one or two individuals that

00:20:58.390 --> 00:21:01.427 align:middle line:84%
have this idea, but a lot of
people have the same idea.

00:21:01.427 --> 00:21:04.497 align:middle line:84%
Some people carry the idea
out, and they get known for it.

00:21:04.497 --> 00:21:06.465 align:middle line:84%
But other people were
having the ideas, too.

00:21:06.465 --> 00:21:08.234 align:middle line:84%
They may decide it
was just a fantasy.

00:21:08.234 --> 00:21:09.435 align:middle line:90%
Or I don't want to do that.

00:21:09.435 --> 00:21:10.669 align:middle line:90%
Or whatever.

00:21:10.669 --> 00:21:13.672 align:middle line:84%
But once an idea starts
to-- once the dreamer starts

00:21:13.672 --> 00:21:17.776 align:middle line:84%
to dream, then the dream
begins to manifest.

00:21:17.776 --> 00:21:19.545 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So then, how
can we, indeed, affect

00:21:19.545 --> 00:21:21.313 align:middle line:90%
our future with this concept?

00:21:21.313 --> 00:21:24.016 align:middle line:84%
How can we start to
project into the future

00:21:24.016 --> 00:21:26.485 align:middle line:90%
with the concept of the dreamer?

00:21:26.485 --> 00:21:28.787 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Well, that's
what the dreamer is.

00:21:28.787 --> 00:21:31.290 align:middle line:84%
The dreamer is in
the future already.

00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:34.593 align:middle line:90%
So the dreamer is already there.

00:21:34.593 --> 00:21:35.895 align:middle line:90%
And there are multiple dreams.

00:21:35.895 --> 00:21:39.832 align:middle line:84%
There are many different
possible dreams of the future,

00:21:39.832 --> 00:21:40.966 align:middle line:90%
from your perspective.

00:21:40.966 --> 00:21:43.636 align:middle line:84%
But you've got to remember
you are the dreamer,

00:21:43.636 --> 00:21:46.939 align:middle line:84%
and the future is
already where you're at.

00:21:46.939 --> 00:21:49.875 align:middle line:84%
So, now you have
to figure out a way

00:21:49.875 --> 00:21:53.979 align:middle line:84%
to connect where you're at
to where you think you are,

00:21:53.979 --> 00:21:55.748 align:middle line:84%
which is like in
the here and now.

00:21:55.748 --> 00:22:01.353 align:middle line:84%
So in some courses in
positive thinking or whatever,

00:22:01.353 --> 00:22:04.857 align:middle line:84%
they tell you to realize
your goals by pretending

00:22:04.857 --> 00:22:08.194 align:middle line:84%
you're already have really--
I want to be a millionaire,

00:22:08.194 --> 00:22:11.430 align:middle line:84%
well think of yourself as having
a million dollars right now.

00:22:11.430 --> 00:22:13.432 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's the dreamer
in the future of you

00:22:13.432 --> 00:22:16.035 align:middle line:84%
as a millionaire reaching back
to where you are right now.

00:22:16.035 --> 00:22:16.769 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All right.

00:22:16.769 --> 00:22:18.671 align:middle line:84%
I want to get back to
our Facebook questions.

00:22:18.671 --> 00:22:20.806 align:middle line:84%
And so, thank you very
much for bringing us--

00:22:20.806 --> 00:22:23.409 align:middle line:84%
for communicating with us
via Facebook and Twitter.

00:22:23.409 --> 00:22:25.678 align:middle line:84%
So do you believe that your
mind-- Judy from Facebook

00:22:25.678 --> 00:22:28.147 align:middle line:84%
asks do you believe that
your mind is powerful enough

00:22:28.147 --> 00:22:29.315 align:middle line:90%
to heal the body?

00:22:29.315 --> 00:22:31.750 align:middle line:84%
And is there any science
in quantum physics

00:22:31.750 --> 00:22:34.553 align:middle line:90%
that actually proves that?

00:22:34.553 --> 00:22:39.358 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: The body mind
has got mind in it.

00:22:39.358 --> 00:22:44.063 align:middle line:84%
So healing cannot take
place without mind.

00:22:44.063 --> 00:22:46.999 align:middle line:84%
If you want to see something
try to heal itself,

00:22:46.999 --> 00:22:52.004 align:middle line:84%
watch a bar of iron
that has a nick in it.

00:22:52.004 --> 00:22:52.771 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's not--

00:22:52.771 --> 00:22:54.640 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: It'll rust over,
but it ain't going to heal,

00:22:54.640 --> 00:22:56.942 align:middle line:84%
because there's not much
mind stuff going on there.

00:22:56.942 --> 00:22:58.911 align:middle line:90%
There's some, but not much.

00:22:58.911 --> 00:23:01.146 align:middle line:84%
But you cut your
finger and suddenly you

00:23:01.146 --> 00:23:04.917 align:middle line:90%
see the body mind acting.

00:23:04.917 --> 00:23:06.719 align:middle line:84%
You might be able
to even influence

00:23:06.719 --> 00:23:07.920 align:middle line:90%
with your conscious mind.

00:23:07.920 --> 00:23:10.122 align:middle line:84%
In other words, you may
actually influence or change

00:23:10.122 --> 00:23:11.056 align:middle line:90%
the healing pattern.

00:23:11.056 --> 00:23:12.324 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is so interesting.

00:23:12.324 --> 00:23:14.893 align:middle line:84%
So we can, with our minds,
really affect our healing.

00:23:14.893 --> 00:23:17.162 align:middle line:84%
We can also adversely
affect our disease.

00:23:17.162 --> 00:23:17.663 align:middle line:90%
We can--

00:23:17.663 --> 00:23:20.866 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: We can also
adversely affect our healing.

00:23:20.866 --> 00:23:23.269 align:middle line:84%
So there are many
things that we can do--

00:23:23.269 --> 00:23:23.469 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's-- yeah--

00:23:23.469 --> 00:23:23.869 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: And with--

00:23:23.869 --> 00:23:24.303 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what
I meant by disease.

00:23:24.303 --> 00:23:24.803 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:23:24.803 --> 00:23:27.506 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: And it's a
question-- right now,

00:23:27.506 --> 00:23:30.042 align:middle line:84%
how much do you want to pay
attention to in your body?

00:23:30.042 --> 00:23:32.411 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I want to pay attention
to the health of my body.

00:23:32.411 --> 00:23:33.979 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: OK, well,
what does that mean?

00:23:33.979 --> 00:23:36.982 align:middle line:84%
For example, do you
want to pay attention

00:23:36.982 --> 00:23:42.221 align:middle line:84%
to the blood which is moving
through your heart right now?

00:23:42.221 --> 00:23:44.623 align:middle line:90%
Do you want to watch that?

00:23:44.623 --> 00:23:45.224 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:23:45.224 --> 00:23:45.758 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Yeah?

00:23:45.758 --> 00:23:46.058 align:middle line:90%
Do you?

00:23:46.058 --> 00:23:46.925 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why not?

00:23:46.925 --> 00:23:47.826 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Well, yeah.

00:23:47.826 --> 00:23:51.930 align:middle line:84%
Well, suppose you have
negative thoughts, something

00:23:51.930 --> 00:23:52.531 align:middle line:90%
that comes up.

00:23:52.531 --> 00:23:54.133 align:middle line:84%
Is that-- you want to be
able to stop your blood

00:23:54.133 --> 00:23:54.867 align:middle line:90%
from flowing in your heart?

00:23:54.867 --> 00:23:55.134 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:23:55.134 --> 00:23:55.634 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: No.

00:23:55.634 --> 00:23:59.038 align:middle line:84%
So there are certain autonomic
functions of your body

00:23:59.038 --> 00:24:00.939 align:middle line:84%
that you just don't want
to pay attention to.

00:24:00.939 --> 00:24:01.707 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, I see.

00:24:01.707 --> 00:24:02.574 align:middle line:90%
I see what you're saying.

00:24:02.574 --> 00:24:04.576 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: You don't want
to mess around with that.

00:24:04.576 --> 00:24:05.978 align:middle line:90%
You can.

00:24:05.978 --> 00:24:07.146 align:middle line:90%
Yogis do it.

00:24:07.146 --> 00:24:09.615 align:middle line:84%
But you have to be careful
when you start messing around

00:24:09.615 --> 00:24:12.217 align:middle line:84%
with things which are pretty
much doing what they're

00:24:12.217 --> 00:24:14.153 align:middle line:84%
supposed to be doing
without you messing around

00:24:14.153 --> 00:24:15.587 align:middle line:90%
with your conscious mind.

00:24:15.587 --> 00:24:19.024 align:middle line:84%
So, there's a certain
amount of let it be.

00:24:19.024 --> 00:24:20.859 align:middle line:90%
Let it be.

00:24:20.859 --> 00:24:26.165 align:middle line:84%
It's got a million years
of genetic evolution

00:24:26.165 --> 00:24:28.033 align:middle line:84%
which has given you
the ability to not

00:24:28.033 --> 00:24:32.204 align:middle line:84%
have to think about that stuff,
so why you want to get into it?

00:24:32.204 --> 00:24:34.973 align:middle line:84%
What do you expect to
gain from getting into it?

00:24:34.973 --> 00:24:36.475 align:middle line:84%
That's the question
you have to ask.

00:24:36.475 --> 00:24:39.011 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So, and as
quantum physics also says,

00:24:39.011 --> 00:24:40.446 align:middle line:90%
let it be and let it go.

00:24:40.446 --> 00:24:42.114 align:middle line:84%
Really, I never
really thought about

00:24:42.114 --> 00:24:44.216 align:middle line:84%
that quantum physics
explains that--

00:24:44.216 --> 00:24:44.717 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Yes.

00:24:44.717 --> 00:24:45.884 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --in such clarity.

00:24:45.884 --> 00:24:47.252 align:middle line:84%
Could you explain that
a little bit for us?

00:24:47.252 --> 00:24:48.987 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Well, basically,
it's a question

00:24:48.987 --> 00:24:53.325 align:middle line:84%
of what it means to learn
to do something which

00:24:53.325 --> 00:24:57.329 align:middle line:84%
is, I would say, not
letting it being, but more

00:24:57.329 --> 00:25:00.366 align:middle line:84%
or less focusing on
how to make it better,

00:25:00.366 --> 00:25:03.836 align:middle line:84%
creating it, and letting it
go, which means allowing more

00:25:03.836 --> 00:25:07.539 align:middle line:84%
possibilities to enter so that
you can change what you have

00:25:07.539 --> 00:25:08.574 align:middle line:90%
or what you're doing.

00:25:08.574 --> 00:25:09.074 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:25:09.074 --> 00:25:09.375 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:25:09.375 --> 00:25:09.975 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:25:09.975 --> 00:25:13.078 align:middle line:84%
So, God, great question from
our Facebook listener, Mark.

00:25:13.078 --> 00:25:19.551 align:middle line:84%
Why do you think physics is
not taught in high school?

00:25:19.551 --> 00:25:21.286 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: It's what do
you think about how

00:25:21.286 --> 00:25:22.488 align:middle line:84%
physics is taught
in high school?

00:25:22.488 --> 00:25:23.589 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, about how
physics is taught.

00:25:23.589 --> 00:25:24.123 align:middle line:90%
OK, great.

00:25:24.123 --> 00:25:24.890 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: OK.

00:25:24.890 --> 00:25:26.058 align:middle line:90%
What do I think about that?

00:25:26.058 --> 00:25:30.095 align:middle line:84%
Well, it depends on the
high school teacher.

00:25:30.095 --> 00:25:34.066 align:middle line:84%
Physics is very much
a very personal thing.

00:25:34.066 --> 00:25:40.239 align:middle line:84%
And the teacher has a lot to do
with how the course is taught.

00:25:40.239 --> 00:25:42.574 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Someone like you
who's dynamic and cares

00:25:42.574 --> 00:25:45.577 align:middle line:84%
really can get the concepts
across in a colorful way

00:25:45.577 --> 00:25:46.612 align:middle line:90%
would be helpful.

00:25:46.612 --> 00:25:48.147 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: That depends
on the students.

00:25:48.147 --> 00:25:48.714 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It does?

00:25:48.714 --> 00:25:50.015 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Yes, of course it does.

00:25:50.015 --> 00:25:53.218 align:middle line:84%
Because students
who take physics

00:25:53.218 --> 00:25:55.754 align:middle line:84%
can take physics for
various different reasons.

00:25:55.754 --> 00:25:58.157 align:middle line:84%
One is it's required,
and I gotta take it,

00:25:58.157 --> 00:25:59.057 align:middle line:90%
but I don't like it.

00:25:59.057 --> 00:26:00.626 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, I
don't understand it.

00:26:00.626 --> 00:26:02.161 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: I don't
understand any of it.

00:26:02.161 --> 00:26:04.296 align:middle line:84%
What has it got to
do with my sex life?

00:26:04.296 --> 00:26:06.365 align:middle line:84%
What is it got to do
with my making money?

00:26:06.365 --> 00:26:08.901 align:middle line:84%
Who's got-- it has everything
to do with all those things.

00:26:08.901 --> 00:26:09.334 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I was about
to say, doesn't it?

00:26:09.334 --> 00:26:09.668 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:26:09.668 --> 00:26:10.736 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Everything to do
with all those things.

00:26:10.736 --> 00:26:12.838 align:middle line:84%
But unless you're
willing to learn that,

00:26:12.838 --> 00:26:15.174 align:middle line:84%
you're not going to ever
really understand that.

00:26:15.174 --> 00:26:18.811 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot that
physics has to do,

00:26:18.811 --> 00:26:22.848 align:middle line:84%
and the best way,
I think, is to have

00:26:22.848 --> 00:26:25.083 align:middle line:84%
enthusiastic
teachers teaching it.

00:26:25.083 --> 00:26:26.618 align:middle line:84%
That's all it really
takes, is just

00:26:26.618 --> 00:26:29.354 align:middle line:84%
to have an enthusiasm
and a desire

00:26:29.354 --> 00:26:34.827 align:middle line:84%
to ignite that thing which gets
ignited when you understand

00:26:34.827 --> 00:26:36.695 align:middle line:90%
something for the first time.

00:26:36.695 --> 00:26:38.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: See, and
those who really

00:26:38.130 --> 00:26:39.531 align:middle line:90%
adhere to it understand it.

00:26:39.531 --> 00:26:41.633 align:middle line:90%
It does take a stretch of mind.

00:26:41.633 --> 00:26:44.570 align:middle line:84%
It gets you out of your
current everyday survival,

00:26:44.570 --> 00:26:48.774 align:middle line:84%
when you really understand the
vastness of quantum physics.

00:26:48.774 --> 00:26:50.375 align:middle line:90%
And I absolutely love that, too.

00:26:50.375 --> 00:26:53.212 align:middle line:84%
What does physics have to do
with making money, by the way?

00:26:53.212 --> 00:26:54.379 align:middle line:90%
Just curious.

00:26:54.379 --> 00:26:55.681 align:middle line:90%
I know this isn't our topic.

00:26:55.681 --> 00:26:57.516 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at
our Facebook questions

00:26:57.516 --> 00:26:59.251 align:middle line:84%
and asking what
someone's asking that.

00:26:59.251 --> 00:27:00.385 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Well, let's see.

00:27:00.385 --> 00:27:02.654 align:middle line:90%
How about Steve Jobs?

00:27:02.654 --> 00:27:03.355 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:27:03.355 --> 00:27:05.290 align:middle line:84%
And how did he relate
physics to making money?

00:27:05.290 --> 00:27:08.093 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: Well, what in all
heaven's name is a computer

00:27:08.093 --> 00:27:10.095 align:middle line:90%
but applied physics?

00:27:10.095 --> 00:27:14.900 align:middle line:90%
And have you ever heard of HD?

00:27:14.900 --> 00:27:19.371 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever heard
of-- all right.

00:27:19.371 --> 00:27:21.340 align:middle line:84%
Almost every single
device-- I mean,

00:27:21.340 --> 00:27:23.909 align:middle line:84%
you've got-- you're
carrying quantum physics

00:27:23.909 --> 00:27:26.478 align:middle line:84%
in your hand with your
Apple phone, or your iPhone,

00:27:26.478 --> 00:27:27.880 align:middle line:90%
or whatever you're using.

00:27:27.880 --> 00:27:30.015 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's all based
upon quantum physics.

00:27:30.015 --> 00:27:33.252 align:middle line:84%
It was discovered based upon the
principles of quantum physics.

00:27:33.252 --> 00:27:35.587 align:middle line:84%
Those things don't work
without quantum physics.

00:27:35.587 --> 00:27:37.856 align:middle line:90%
So how does physics make money?

00:27:37.856 --> 00:27:39.958 align:middle line:84%
I mean, my God, you ever
heard of the internet?

00:27:39.958 --> 00:27:42.160 align:middle line:84%
I mean none of that is even
possible without quantum

00:27:42.160 --> 00:27:42.661 align:middle line:90%
physics.

00:27:42.661 --> 00:27:43.362 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Because--

00:27:43.362 --> 00:27:44.796 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: And who
knows what's next.

00:27:44.796 --> 00:27:48.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because it connects
space, time, and matter?

00:27:48.100 --> 00:27:49.234 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: It connects us all.

00:27:49.234 --> 00:27:50.869 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's opened
up the whole door--

00:27:50.869 --> 00:27:51.637 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Beautiful.

00:27:51.637 --> 00:27:52.738 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: --to communication.

00:27:52.738 --> 00:27:57.342 align:middle line:84%
So quantum physics has been--
we're living in the quantum

00:27:57.342 --> 00:27:59.845 align:middle line:90%
age, and it's still developing.

00:27:59.845 --> 00:28:01.280 align:middle line:84%
We're getting into
quantum biology.

00:28:01.280 --> 00:28:02.748 align:middle line:84%
We're wanting to
change our lives.

00:28:02.748 --> 00:28:04.116 align:middle line:90%
We're putting in--

00:28:04.116 --> 00:28:04.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Stem cells--

00:28:04.950 --> 00:28:05.250 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: --drugs.

00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:05.751 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --and whatever.

00:28:05.751 --> 00:28:06.184 align:middle line:90%
>>FRED: Stem cells.

00:28:06.184 --> 00:28:07.786 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's so
much we're doing

00:28:07.786 --> 00:28:09.121 align:middle line:90%
right now that's based upon--

00:28:09.121 --> 00:28:09.588 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Quantum physics.

00:28:09.588 --> 00:28:10.956 align:middle line:84%
>>FRED: --the
understanding we've

00:28:10.956 --> 00:28:13.091 align:middle line:84%
got from-- without
quantum physics,

00:28:13.091 --> 00:28:14.993 align:middle line:84%
we never would have
understood DNA.

00:28:14.993 --> 00:28:15.661 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Amazing.

00:28:15.661 --> 00:28:17.262 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely amazing, this
is what I'm talking about.

00:28:17.262 --> 00:28:18.330 align:middle line:90%
Fred Allan Wolfe is my guest.

00:28:18.330 --> 00:28:19.731 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
take a quick break.

00:28:19.731 --> 00:28:22.901 align:middle line:84%
But we're talking about how to
bring in the concept of quantum

00:28:22.901 --> 00:28:24.770 align:middle line:90%
physics to your everyday life.

00:28:24.770 --> 00:28:27.272 align:middle line:84%
How to live a quantum
life, essentially.

00:28:27.272 --> 00:28:28.540 align:middle line:90%
We see it all around us.

00:28:28.540 --> 00:28:30.709 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much for
illuminating that for us.

00:28:30.709 --> 00:28:31.577 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate it.

